What you need to know:  Mr Odinga and his running mate Martha Karua, who spoke in Bomet and Kericho counties, also said their government would not harass the opposition.Mr Odinga backed calls by Central Organisation of Trade Unions Secretary-General Francis Atwoli to end the use of the machines in tea plantations.Multinationals and local firms that have introduced tea plucking machines include Unilever, James Finlays, Sotik Tea and George Williamson.